{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2040,"text":"Vanessa Garrison: I am Vanessa,"},{"time":3800,"text":"daughter of Annette,"},{"time":5440,"text":"daughter of Olympia,"},{"time":7240,"text":"daughter of Melvina,"},{"time":8800,"text":"daughter of Katie, born 1878,"},{"time":12120,"text":"Parish County, Louisiana."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14600,"text":"T. Morgan Dixon: And my name is Morgan,"},{"time":16520,"text":"daughter of Carol,\ndaughter of Letha, daughter of Willie,"},{"time":19280,"text":"daughter of Sarah,\nborn 1849 in Bardstown, Kentucky."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23680,"text":"VG: And in the tradition of our families,"},{"time":25720,"text":"the great oral tradition\nof almost every black church we know"},{"time":29040,"text":"honoring the culture\nfrom which we draw so much power,"},{"time":32960,"text":"we're gonna start the way our mommas\nand grandmas would want us to start."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36440,"text":"TMD: In prayer. Let the words of my mouth,"},{"time":39120,"text":"the meditation of our hearts,\nbe acceptable in thy sight,"},{"time":42280,"text":"oh Lord, my strength and my redeemer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46000,"text":"VG: We call the names and rituals\nof our ancestors into this room today"},{"time":50520,"text":"because from them we received\na powerful blueprint for survival,"},{"time":55000,"text":"strategies and tactics for healing\ncarried across oceans by African women,"},{"time":59600,"text":"passed down to generations\nof black women in America"},{"time":62960,"text":"who used those skills\nto navigate institutions of slavery"},{"time":67320,"text":"and state-sponsored discrimination"},{"time":69240,"text":"in order that we might\nstand on this stage."},{"time":72560,"text":"We walk in the footsteps of those women,"},{"time":75320,"text":"our foremothers, legends"},{"time":77640,"text":"like Ella Baker, Septima Clark,\nFannie Lou Hamer,"},{"time":81600,"text":"from whom we learned\nthe power of organizing"},{"time":84520,"text":"after she would had\nsingle-handedly registered"},{"time":87480,"text":"60,000 voters in Jim Crow Mississippi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91680,"text":"TMD: 60,000 is a lot of people,\nso if you can imagine"},{"time":95360,"text":"me and Vanessa inspiring\n60,000 women to walk with us last year,"},{"time":99840,"text":"we were fired up."},{"time":101840,"text":"But today, 100,000 black women and girls\nstand on this stage with us."},{"time":107800,"text":"We are committed to healing ourselves,"},{"time":110480,"text":"to lacing up our sneakers,\nto walking out of our front door"},{"time":113280,"text":"every single day for total healing\nand transformation in our communities,"},{"time":116840,"text":"because we understand"},{"time":118480,"text":"that we are in the footsteps\nof a civil rights legacy"},{"time":121000,"text":"like no other time before,"},{"time":123120,"text":"and that we are facing a health crisis\nlike never ever before."},{"time":126080,"text":"And so we've had\na lot of moments, great moments,"},{"time":129120,"text":"including the time we had on our pajamas,\nwe were working on our computer"},{"time":132600,"text":"and Michelle Obama emailed us\nand invited us to the White House,"},{"time":135680,"text":"and we thought it was spam."},{"time":137080,"text":"But this moment here is an opportunity."},{"time":140520,"text":"It is an opportunity\nthat we don't take for granted,"},{"time":143280,"text":"and so we thought long and hard\nabout how we would use it."},{"time":146040,"text":"Would we talk to the women\nwe hope to inspire,"},{"time":148760,"text":"a million in the next year,"},{"time":150520,"text":"or would we talk to you?"},{"time":152960,"text":"We decided to talk to you,"},{"time":155240,"text":"and to talk to you about a question\nthat we get all the time,"},{"time":159840,"text":"so that the millions of women\nwho hopefully will watch this"},{"time":162680,"text":"will never have to answer it again."},{"time":165080,"text":"It is: Why are black women dying"},{"time":168160,"text":"faster and at higher rates"},{"time":170120,"text":"than any other group of people in America"},{"time":172600,"text":"from preventable,\nobesity-related diseases?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":176760,"text":"The question hurts me."},{"time":178200,"text":"I'm shaking a little bit."},{"time":179640,"text":"It feels value-laden."},{"time":181320,"text":"It hurts my body because the weight\nrepresents so much."},{"time":185280,"text":"But we're going to talk about it"},{"time":186880,"text":"and invite you into\nan inside conversation today"},{"time":189160,"text":"because it is necessary,\nand because we need you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194120,"text":"VG: Each night,\nbefore the first day of school,"},{"time":196360,"text":"my grandmother\nwould sit me next to the stove"},{"time":199040,"text":"and with expert precision\nuse a hot comb to press my hair."},{"time":202880,"text":"My grandmother was legendary, big, loud."},{"time":206400,"text":"She filled up a room with laughter\nand oftentimes curse words."},{"time":209360,"text":"She cooked a mean peach cobbler,"},{"time":211360,"text":"had 11 children,\na house full of grandchildren,"},{"time":213920,"text":"and like every black woman I know,"},{"time":216400,"text":"like most all women I know,"},{"time":218160,"text":"she had prioritized the care of others\nover caring for herself."},{"time":222520,"text":"We measured her strength by her capacity\nto endure pain and suffering."},{"time":226280,"text":"We celebrated her for it,\nand our choice would prove to be deadly."},{"time":230160,"text":"One night after pressing my hair\nbefore the first day of eighth grade,"},{"time":233520,"text":"my grandmother went to bed\nand never woke up,"},{"time":236360,"text":"dead at 66 years old from a heart attack."},{"time":239720,"text":"By the time I would graduate college,"},{"time":241600,"text":"I would lose two more beloved\nfamily members to chronic disease:"},{"time":245120,"text":"my aunt Diane, dead at 55,\nmy aunt Tricia, dead at 63."},{"time":249480,"text":"After living with these losses,\nthe hole that they left,"},{"time":252320,"text":"I decided to calculate the life expectancy\nof the women in my family."},{"time":256839,"text":"Staring back at me, the number 65."},{"time":260320,"text":"I knew I could not sit by"},{"time":261920,"text":"and watch another woman I loved\ndie an early death."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266160,"text":"TMD: So we don't usually\nput our business in the streets."},{"time":268880,"text":"Let's just put that out there."},{"time":270360,"text":"But I have to tell you the statistics."},{"time":272320,"text":"Black women are dying at alarming rates,"},{"time":275120,"text":"and I used to be a classroom teacher,"},{"time":277000,"text":"and I was at South Atlanta High School,"},{"time":278920,"text":"and I remember standing\nin front of my classroom,"},{"time":281280,"text":"and I remember a statistic\nthat half of black girls will get diabetes"},{"time":286000,"text":"unless diet and levels of activity change."},{"time":288800,"text":"Half of the girls in my classroom.\nSo I couldn't teach anymore."},{"time":292360,"text":"So I started taking girls hiking,\nwhich is why we're called GirlTrek,"},{"time":295640,"text":"but Vanessa was like,"},{"time":296880,"text":"that is not going to move the dial\non the health crisis; it's cute."},{"time":300080,"text":"She was like, it's a cute hiking club."},{"time":301960,"text":"So what we thought"},{"time":303640,"text":"is if we could rally\na million of their mothers ..."},{"time":308960,"text":"82 percent of black women\nare over a healthy weight right now."},{"time":312320,"text":"53 percent of us are obese."},{"time":317000,"text":"But the number that I cannot,"},{"time":319840,"text":"that I cannot get out of my head"},{"time":321440,"text":"is that every single day in America,"},{"time":324840,"text":"137 black women"},{"time":327400,"text":"die from a preventable disease,"},{"time":329520,"text":"heart disease."},{"time":330760,"text":"That's every 11 minutes."},{"time":332920,"text":"137 is more than gun violence,"},{"time":336160,"text":"cigarette smoking and HIV combined,"},{"time":339680,"text":"every day."},{"time":341040,"text":"It is roughly the amount of people"},{"time":342720,"text":"that were on my plane\nfrom New Jersey to Vancouver."},{"time":345640,"text":"Can you imagine that?"},{"time":346880,"text":"A plane filled with black women\ncrashing to the ground every day,"},{"time":351360,"text":"and no one is talking about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354600,"text":"VG: So the question that you're all\nasking yourselves right now is why?"},{"time":357960,"text":"Why are black women dying?\nWe asked ourselves that same question."},{"time":361080,"text":"Why is what's out there\nnot working for them?"},{"time":363520,"text":"Private weight loss companies,\ngovernment interventions,"},{"time":366200,"text":"public health campaigns."},{"time":367560,"text":"I'm going to tell you why:"},{"time":369040,"text":"because they focus on weight loss"},{"time":370680,"text":"or looking good in skinny jeans"},{"time":372200,"text":"without acknowledging the trauma"},{"time":374240,"text":"that black women\nhold in our bellies and bones,"},{"time":377160,"text":"that has been embedded in our very DNA."},{"time":380000,"text":"The best advice\nfrom hospitals and doctors,"},{"time":382360,"text":"the best medications\nfrom pharmaceutical companies"},{"time":384880,"text":"to treat the congestive heart failure\nof my grandmother didn't work"},{"time":388280,"text":"because they didn't acknowledge\nthe systemic racism"},{"time":390920,"text":"that she had dealt with since birth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392680,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":393720,"text":"A divestment in schools,\ndiscriminatory housing practices,"},{"time":397080,"text":"predatory lending,\na crack cocaine epidemic,"},{"time":400160,"text":"mass incarceration putting\nmore black bodies behind bars"},{"time":403560,"text":"than were owned at the height of slavery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405800,"text":"But GirlTrek does."},{"time":407600,"text":"For black women whose bodies\nare buckling under the weight"},{"time":410360,"text":"of systems never designed to support them,"},{"time":413080,"text":"GirlTrek is a lifeline."},{"time":415160,"text":"August 16, 2015, Danita Kimball,\na member of GirlTrek in Detroit,"},{"time":419760,"text":"received the news that too many\nblack mothers have received."},{"time":423040,"text":"Her son Norman, 23 years old,\na father of two,"},{"time":426440,"text":"was gunned down\nwhile on an afternoon drive."},{"time":429440,"text":"Imagine the grief"},{"time":431160,"text":"that overcomes your body in that moment,"},{"time":433600,"text":"the immobilizing fear."},{"time":435920,"text":"Now, know this, that just days\nafter laying her son to rest,"},{"time":439440,"text":"Danita Kimball posted online,"},{"time":441200,"text":"\"I don't know what to do\nor how to move forward,"},{"time":443960,"text":"but my sisters keep telling me\nI need to walk, so I will.\""},{"time":447000,"text":"And then just days after that,"},{"time":449560,"text":"\"I got my steps in today for my baby Norm."},{"time":451840,"text":"It felt good to be out there, to walk.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":456480,"text":"TMD: Walking through pain\nis what we have always done."},{"time":459040,"text":"My mom, she's in the middle right there,"},{"time":462240,"text":"my mom desegregated\nher high school in 1955."},{"time":465600,"text":"Her mom walked down the steps\nof an abandoned school bus"},{"time":468360,"text":"where she raised 11 kids\nas a sharecropper."},{"time":471280,"text":"And her mom stepped onto Indian territory"},{"time":473480,"text":"fleeing the terrors of the Jim Crow South."},{"time":476160,"text":"And her mom walked her man to the door"},{"time":479160,"text":"as he went off to fight\nin the Kentucky Colored Regiment,"},{"time":482640,"text":"the Civil War."},{"time":484360,"text":"They were born slaves\nbut they wouldn't die slaves."},{"time":486800,"text":"Change-making, it's in my blood."},{"time":488720,"text":"It's what I do,"},{"time":490000,"text":"and this health crisis ain't nothing\ncompared to the road we have traveled."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495960,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":500920,"text":"So it's like James Cleveland."},{"time":502360,"text":"I don't feel no ways tired,\nso we got to work."},{"time":504920,"text":"We started looking at models of change."},{"time":507000,"text":"We looked all over the world."},{"time":508440,"text":"We needed something"},{"time":509680,"text":"not only that was a part\nof our cultural inheritance like walking,"},{"time":512840,"text":"but something that was scalable,\nsomething that was high-impact,"},{"time":515919,"text":"something that we could replicate\nacross this country."},{"time":518520,"text":"So we studied models like Wangari Maathai,\nwho won the Nobel Peace Prize"},{"time":521960,"text":"for inspiring women\nto plant 50 million trees in Kenya."},{"time":524600,"text":"She brought Kenya back from the brink\nof environmental devastation."},{"time":527800,"text":"We studied these systems of change,\nand we looked at walking scientifically."},{"time":532200,"text":"And what we learned\nis that walking just 30 minutes a day"},{"time":535280,"text":"can single-handedly decrease\n50 percent of your risk of diabetes,"},{"time":540560,"text":"heart disease, stroke,\neven Alzheimer's and dementia."},{"time":544600,"text":"We know that walking\nis the single most powerful thing"},{"time":548640,"text":"that a woman can do for her health,"},{"time":550800,"text":"so we knew we were on to something,"},{"time":552600,"text":"because from Harriet Tubman\nto the women in Montgomery,"},{"time":555240,"text":"when black women walk, things change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557080,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":558120,"text":"VG: So how did we take\nthis simple idea of walking"},{"time":560680,"text":"and start a revolution\nthat would catch a fire"},{"time":562880,"text":"in neighborhoods across America?"},{"time":564840,"text":"We used the best practices\nof the Civil Rights Movement."},{"time":567760,"text":"We huddled up in church basements."},{"time":569440,"text":"We did grapevine information sharing\nthrough beauty salons."},{"time":572360,"text":"We empowered and trained mothers\nto stand on the front lines."},{"time":575280,"text":"We took our message\ndirectly to the streets,"},{"time":577800,"text":"and women responded."},{"time":579240,"text":"Women like LaKeisha in Chattanooga,"},{"time":581600,"text":"Chrysantha in Detroit,"},{"time":583840,"text":"Onika in New Orleans,"},{"time":585400,"text":"women with difficult names\nand difficult stories"},{"time":588360,"text":"join GirlTrek every day and commit\nto walking as a practice of self-care."},{"time":593280,"text":"Once walking, those women\nget to organizing,"},{"time":595760,"text":"first their families,\nthen their communities,"},{"time":597920,"text":"to walk and talk\nand solve problems together."},{"time":600760,"text":"They walk and notice\nthe abandoned building."},{"time":602880,"text":"They walk and notice\nthe lack of sidewalks,"},{"time":604920,"text":"the lack of green space,"},{"time":606200,"text":"and they say, \"No more.\""},{"time":607480,"text":"Women like Susie Paige in Philadelphia,"},{"time":609400,"text":"who after walking daily past\nan abandoned building in her neighborhood,"},{"time":612920,"text":"decided, \"I'm not waiting."},{"time":614400,"text":"Let me rally my team.\nLet me grab some supplies."},{"time":616760,"text":"Let me do what no one else has done\nfor me and my community.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":621720,"text":"TMD: We know one woman\ncan make a difference,"},{"time":623880,"text":"because one woman\nhas already changed the world,"},{"time":626160,"text":"and her name is Harriet Tubman."},{"time":627720,"text":"And trust me, I love Harriet Tubman."},{"time":630120,"text":"I'm obsessed with her,\nand I used to be a history teacher."},{"time":632880,"text":"I will not tell you the whole history."},{"time":634760,"text":"I will tell you four things."},{"time":636160,"text":"So I used to have an old Saab --"},{"time":638200,"text":"the kind of canvas top that drips\non your head when it rains --"},{"time":641200,"text":"and I drove all the way down\nto the eastern shore of Maryland,"},{"time":644129,"text":"and when I stepped on the dirt"},{"time":645600,"text":"that Harriet Tubman made her first escape,"},{"time":648560,"text":"I knew she was a woman just like we are"},{"time":650680,"text":"and that we could do what she had done,"},{"time":652600,"text":"and we learned four things\nfrom Harriet Tubman."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654920,"text":"The first one: do not wait."},{"time":657720,"text":"Walk right now in the direction\nof your healthiest, most fulfilled life,"},{"time":662240,"text":"because self-care is a revolutionary act."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665000,"text":"Number two:"},{"time":666360,"text":"when you learn the way forward,\ncome back and get a sister."},{"time":669600,"text":"So in our case,\nstart a team with your friends --"},{"time":671960,"text":"your friends, your family, your church."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673880,"text":"Number three:"},{"time":675520,"text":"rally your allies."},{"time":679000,"text":"Every single person in this room"},{"time":681880,"text":"is complicit in\na Tubman-inspired takeover."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685000,"text":"And number four:"},{"time":686880,"text":"find joy."},{"time":688920,"text":"The most underreported\nfact of Harriet Tubman"},{"time":691200,"text":"is that she lived to be 93 years old,"},{"time":693760,"text":"and she didn't live\njust an ordinary life; uh-uh."},{"time":696120,"text":"She was standing up for the good guys.\nShe married a younger man."},{"time":699240,"text":"She adopted a child.\nI'm not kidding. She lived."},{"time":702480,"text":"And I drove up to her house\nof freedom in upstate New York,"},{"time":705320,"text":"and she had planted apple trees,"},{"time":707240,"text":"and when I was there on a Sunday,\nthey were blooming."},{"time":709920,"text":"Do you call it -- do they bloom?"},{"time":711520,"text":"The apples were in season,"},{"time":713240,"text":"and I was thinking, she left fruit for us,"},{"time":716760,"text":"the legacy of Harriet Tubman,\nevery single year."},{"time":720440,"text":"And we know that we are Harriet,"},{"time":722400,"text":"and we know that there is a Harriet\nin every community in America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726560,"text":"VG: We also know that there's a Harriet\nin every community across the globe,"},{"time":730240,"text":"and that they could learn\nfrom our Tubman Doctrine,"},{"time":733040,"text":"as we call it, the four steps."},{"time":735520,"text":"Imagine the possibilities"},{"time":737240,"text":"beyond the neighborhoods\nof Oakland and Newark,"},{"time":739960,"text":"to the women working\nrice fields in Vietnam,"},{"time":742120,"text":"tea fields in Sri Lanka,"},{"time":743720,"text":"the women on the\nmountainsides in Guatemala,"},{"time":746080,"text":"the indigenous reservations\nthroughout the vast plains of the Dakotas."},{"time":749920,"text":"We believe that women walking"},{"time":751480,"text":"and talking together\nto solve their problems"},{"time":753920,"text":"is a global solution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756560,"text":"TMD: And I'll leave you with this,"},{"time":758240,"text":"because we also believe it can become\nthe center of social justice again."},{"time":761920,"text":"Vanessa and I were in Fort Lauderdale."},{"time":763800,"text":"We had an organizer training,"},{"time":765240,"text":"and I was leaving\nand I got on the airplane,"},{"time":767880,"text":"and I saw someone I knew, so I waved,"},{"time":769720,"text":"and as I'm waiting in that long line\nthat you guys know,"},{"time":772400,"text":"waiting for people\nto put their stuff away,"},{"time":774440,"text":"I looked back and I realized I didn't\nknow the woman but I recognized her."},{"time":778160,"text":"And so I blew her a kiss\nbecause it was Sybrina Fulton,"},{"time":781960,"text":"Trayvon Martin's mom,"},{"time":783200,"text":"and she whispered \"thank you\" back to me."},{"time":787000,"text":"And I can't help but wonder\nwhat would happen"},{"time":789520,"text":"if there were groups of women\nwalking on Trayvon's block that day,"},{"time":793400,"text":"or what would happen\nin the South Side of Chicago every day"},{"time":796560,"text":"if there were groups of women\nand mothers and aunts and cousins"},{"time":800240,"text":"walking,"},{"time":801480,"text":"or along the polluted rivers\nof Flint, Michigan."},{"time":805000,"text":"I believe that walking\ncan transform our communities,"},{"time":808040,"text":"because it's already starting to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":810120,"text":"VG: We believe that\nthe personal is political."},{"time":812760,"text":"Our walking is for healing,\nfor joy, for fresh air,"},{"time":815560,"text":"quiet time, to connect\nand disconnect, to worship."},{"time":819440,"text":"But it's also walking\nso we can be healthy enough"},{"time":822480,"text":"to stand on the front lines\nfor change in our communities,"},{"time":826640,"text":"and it is our call to action\nto every black woman listening,"},{"time":830320,"text":"every black woman in earshot of our voice,"},{"time":832640,"text":"every black woman who you know."},{"time":834200,"text":"Think about it: the woman working\nfront desk reception at your job,"},{"time":837400,"text":"the woman who delivers\nyour mail, your neighbor --"},{"time":839800,"text":"our call to action to them,\nto join us on the front lines"},{"time":843280,"text":"for change in your community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":845920,"text":"TMD: And I'll bring us back to this moment"},{"time":848000,"text":"and why it's so important\nfor my dear, dear friend Vanessa and I."},{"time":851200,"text":"It's because it's not always easy for us,"},{"time":853200,"text":"and in fact, we have both seen\nreally, really dark days,"},{"time":857320,"text":"from the hate speech to the summer\nof police brutality and violence"},{"time":861000,"text":"that we saw last year,"},{"time":863200,"text":"to even losing one of our walkers,"},{"time":865000,"text":"Sandy Bland, who died in police custody."},{"time":869880,"text":"But the most courageous thing\nwe do every day is we practice faith"},{"time":873440,"text":"that goes beyond the facts,"},{"time":874800,"text":"and we put feet to our prayers\nevery single day,"},{"time":878640,"text":"and when we get overwhelmed,"},{"time":880320,"text":"we think of the words of people\nlike Sonia Sanchez, a poet laureate,"},{"time":883720,"text":"who says, \"Morgan, where is your fire?"},{"time":886120,"text":"Where is the fire that burned\nholes through slave ships"},{"time":888760,"text":"to make us breathe?"},{"time":890000,"text":"Where is the fire\nthat turned guts into chitlins,"},{"time":892360,"text":"that took rhythms and make jazz,"},{"time":894160,"text":"that took sit-ins and marches\nand made us jump boundaries and barriers?"},{"time":897840,"text":"You've got to find it and pass it on.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":900520,"text":"So this is us finding our fire\nand passing it on to you."},{"time":903920,"text":"So please, stand with us,"},{"time":906280,"text":"walk with us as we rally a million women"},{"time":908920,"text":"to reclaim the streets\nof the 50 highest need communities"},{"time":911840,"text":"in this country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":913240,"text":"We thank you so much for this opportunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":915640,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}